\begin_layout Standard
We need to first consider what the probability of state 2 occurring given
 that both good and bad types will buy the same contract.
 Denote the pooled probability of state 2: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \[
\bar{p}=\lambda p_{G}+(1-\lambda)p_{B}=\left(0.2\times0.1\right)+\left(0.8\times0.6\right)=0.5\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Using equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Expected Profit in s1 and s2"

\end_inset

 (or equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Linear Expected Profit in s1 and s2"

\end_inset

), we can write the actuarily fair line for pooled contracts (
\begin_inset Formula $\overline{AP}$
\end_inset

) as follows: 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula \begin{eqnarray}
\left(W-\bar{p}L\right)-\left(\bar{p}\cdot s_{2}+(1-\bar{p})\cdot s_{1}\right) & = & 0\nonumber \\
\Rightarrow\left(1000-\left(0.5\cdot900\right)\right)-\left(0.5\cdot s_{2}+(1-0.5)\cdot s_{1}\right) & = & 0\nonumber \\
\Rightarrow s_{2}=1100-s_{1}\label{eq:AP}\end{eqnarray}

\end_inset

Note that the slope of the actuarily fair line for the pooled type is equal
